      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:30:6",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ كَسَرَ يَدَ رَجُلٍ ثُمَّ بَرَأَتْ يَدُ الرَّجُلِ قَالَ لَيْسَ فِي هَذَا قِصَاصٌ وَ لَكِنْ يُعْطَى الْأَرْشَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Hadeed, from Jameel Bin Darraj, from one of our companions, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from one of the two (5<sup>th</sup> or 6<sup>th</sup> Imam<sup>asws</sup>) regarding a man who broke a hand of a man, then the hand of the man was cured. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no retaliation regarding this, but he would be given the compensation’."
        ]
      }
